  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nagaraja-cou1-nc7-notaccepted-dr",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-fda-cdrh-credibility-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team lead",
    "outcome": "Not accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for COU1 (non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw, ASTM F1717 static compression-bending) yields a Not-accepted decision based on two documented factor shortfalls at modelRiskLevel 3. (1) Model inputs (required Gradation 3, achieved Gradation 2): material properties were sourced from published MMPDS-12 nominal values rather than lot-specific coupon testing of the actual screw material batch. At Gradation 3 the required level demands lot-specific traceability; the absence of this traceability introduces unquantified batch-to-batch variability that cannot be bounded by the ±2-sigma literature range alone. (2) Test conditions (required Gradation 3, achieved Gradation 2): validation was performed under a single ASTM F1717 static compression-bending configuration. The COU loading envelope includes torsional and cyclic fatigue loading relevant to in vivo use; these were not covered by the validation dataset. A single load configuration satisfies Gradation 2 but not Gradation 3 for a medium model-risk, medium decision-consequence application. Both shortfalls are marginal — the output comparison metrics (E/uval < 1.96 for all three QoIs; percentage differences < 10%) demonstrate that the model performs well within the tested configuration, and the MMPDS-12 material data are well-established for Ti-6Al-4V. Nevertheless, the pre-specified acceptance threshold at Gradation 3 for these two factors is not met, and no offset rationale is being advanced. The credibility evidence as constituted is insufficient to support the claim. Recommended remediation: (a) obtain lot-specific tensile coupon data from the same material batch as the test constructs and re-assess Model inputs; (b) extend validation to include at least one additional load configuration (e.g., ASTM F1717 torsion) and re-assess Test conditions.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
